versions.description:
NOTE:
• Before installing this version, delete the "D.A. Assets" folder;
• Support for D.A. Localizator is temporarily disabled. It will return as soon as the new D.A. Localizator release is completed;

ADDED:
• A new solution for the import issue affecting child objects with complex fills when using UI.Image, described in rule 6 of the Layout Rules in the Designer Manual. The asset can now generate sprites on its own that replicate fills, strokes, and effects for such components, which prevents them from being skipped during import. This does not work for all objects, and you must still follow rule 6 if issues occur with similar parent components;
• The ImageOverflow asset is now included with the Figma Converter, since some sprites described in the previous changelog item require their effects to be rendered outside the RectTransform;

IMPROVED:
• The sprite downloading algorithm. If the total sprite size, including scale, exceeds the limit, the request is now automatically split into smaller batches of sprites, or the scale of individual problematic sprites is reduced. This may increase sprite import time for projects with high-resolution frames, but it makes the import process more stable;
• Smarter matching of the corresponding TTF/TMP/UITK font asset by family, weight, italic, style name, and PostScript name, instead of relying only on the exact file name;

CHANGED:
• JSONNET_PLASTIC_EXISTS was replaced with JSONNET_EXISTS in a significant portion of JSON models and loaders. Newtonsoft.Json is now installed automatically via UPM if it is missing when the asset is imported into an empty project;

FIXED:
• Compatibility with UniText;
• A project build error caused by the Editor dependency;
• An issue where selecting folders in the asset settings saved absolute paths instead of relative ones.
